Bush advisers who once anticipated all-out war with Democrats over his attempts to reshape the Supreme Court have had to recalibrate their strategy to battle an insurrection among Republicans who contend the president was obligated to nominate a top-flight legal figure with an unmistakably conservative pedigree. The president made it clear Friday that he has no intention of backing down. Among the most outspoken detractors was former presidential candidate Pat Buchanan, who, on NBC television's ``Meet the Press'' program, said Bush should name someone else to fill the vacancy on the US high court. 